The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, June 18, 2003 				 Karishma case
																								Calcutta, May 17: Sahara TV counsel Siddhartha Shankar Ray continued his argument in the high court today, contesting the plagiarisation charges levelled against the Sahara Manoranjan channel by Manhattan-based British author Barbara Taylor Bradford. He contested the copyright infringement charges and cited various differences between Karishma: The Miracles of Destiny and Bradfords novel A Woman of Substance. The hearing will continue tomorrow.
